  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Grounding Responsible Research and Innovation (RRI) practices in research performing organisations ( GRRIP)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">GRRIP is an European Funded project ( Horizon 2020) of 4 years aiming at embeding sustainable RRI practices in four European research public organisations and one funding body through Action Plans (AP) for institutional and cultural change. This will be accompanied by establishing a platform for engagement with the Quadruple Helix and a platform for mutual learning . UNESCO will be leading WP 3 reviewing the Status of the Art of RRI and creating a Library of actions on existing practices for public research and funding bodies to promote RRI keys: society engagement, science education, women in science, ethics and open acces.</narrative>
  </description>
